&lt;p data-start=&quot;169&quot; data-end=&quot;594&quot;&gt;BDA is seeking an experienced &lt;strong data-start=&quot;199&quot; data-end=&quot;221&quot;&gt;Payroll Specialist&lt;/strong&gt; with a strong background in &lt;strong data-start=&quot;250&quot; data-end=&quot;299&quot;&gt;domestic and international payroll processing&lt;/strong&gt;, payroll systems, and HRIS support. The ideal candidate will bring at least &lt;strong data-start=&quot;376&quot; data-end=&quot;418&quot;&gt;5 years of hands-on payroll experience&lt;/strong&gt;, strong knowledge of &lt;strong data-start=&quot;440&quot; data-end=&quot;459&quot;&gt;ADP and Workday&lt;/strong&gt;, and advanced &lt;strong data-start=&quot;474&quot; data-end=&quot;490&quot;&gt;Excel skills&lt;/strong&gt; to support detailed reporting, reconciliations, payroll audits, and system-driven process improvements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;596&quot; data-end=&quot;909&quot;&gt;This role is a great fit for someone who enjoys payroll accuracy, compliance, systems optimization, and cross-functional partnership with HR, Finance, and business leaders. Experience supporting or leading Workday implementations, global payroll projects, or HRIS/payroll process improvements is highly preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
