&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Most companies claim to have the best people. We say to them, &quot;Keep dreaming.&quot; Our people are second to none. They set us apart with their entrepreneurial spirit and ambition. They come to us from the likes of Amazon, Microsoft, Nordstrom, Starbucks and the sports world, bringing energy, bold ideas and a willingness to dive into the unfamiliar. It&#39;s our people that make BDA the top global Merchandise Agency to work for.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Freelance Creative Designer – Merchandise &amp;amp; Product Concepts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Remote / Freelance&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Freelance / Project-Based&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company&lt;/strong&gt;: BDA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BDA is looking to connect with talented freelance creative designers who can jump in and support our team when rush projects, overflow work, or specialized creative needs come up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is&lt;strong&gt; not a full-time or consistently scheduled role.&lt;/strong&gt; Instead, we are building a network of trusted freelance partners who are open to taking on project-based work here and there, depending on client needs, timing, and availability. Some projects may come with a defined timeline, while others may move quickly or evolve as the work develops.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This could be a great fit for someone who enjoys variety, moves quickly, and is comfortable jumping into creative projects that help bring brands to life through meaningful, thoughtful, and unexpected merchandise experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Help Create&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;In this freelance role, you may support a wide range of creative deliverables, including custom merchandise concepts, limited-time fan collectibles, product packaging, promotional activations, product presentations, and client-facing visual storytelling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The right freelance partner understands that great merchandise is more than putting a logo on a product. It is about understanding the brand, the audience, the moment, and how a product can create excitement, connection, and memorable customer experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
